OL,3,CAnti-slavery day: 'Global epidemic'
OL,4,Csees 50 million exploited worldwide
OL,6,FIt's a meeting I will never forget.
OL,8,FIt's 2005, and a neighbour knocks on
OL,9,Fmy door. Her name is Juliet Singer and
OL,10,Fshe works for the National Missing
OL,11,FPersons Helpline.
OL,13,FAs part of her work, she is starting
OL,14,Fto come across young women, who've
OL,15,Fbeen brought to the UK under false
OL,16,Fpretenses - their passports held by
OL,17,Fthose who've promised to find them
OL,18,Fwork here - and who are put to hard
OL,19,Flabour, often sex work, to repay the
OL,20,Fdebt they owe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
