OL,3,CAnti-slavery day: 'Global epidemic'
OL,4,Csees 50 million exploited worldwide
OL,6,FOmosovie had been trafficked from
OL,7,FNigeria. Her slave master had promised
OL,8,Fher work in a hotel. Instead, when she
OL,9,Farrived - she was forced to work on
OL,10,Fthe streets, and was beaten if she
OL,11,Frefused.
OL,13,FShe rolled up her sleeve and showed me
OL,14,Fthe marks on her arm where she had
OL,15,Fbeen whipped with a belt. The man had
OL,16,Fkept her passport, and took all of her
OL,17,Fearnings - which he claimed she owed
OL,18,Fhim for the journey to Britain.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
