OL,3,CAnti-slavery day: 'Global epidemic'
OL,4,Csees 50 million exploited worldwide
OL,6,FIn a campaign to mark this year's Anti-
OL,7,FSlavery Day - they have interviewed a
OL,8,Fnumber of figures involved in the
OL,9,Ffight against this pernicious crime.
OL,10,FThey've asked each to describe their
OL,11,F'epiphany' moment with the issue.
OL,13,FOmosovie's story was mine. In the
OL,14,Fnearly 20 years since, when I can,
OL,15,FI've tried to get the stories of those
OL,16,Fwho've been trafficked and enslaved
OL,17,Finto the news.
OL,19,FAnd it's more important than ever.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
