OL,3,CAnti-slavery day: 'Global epidemic'
OL,4,Csees 50 million exploited worldwide
OL,6,FThey made her sleep on her own floor,
OL,7,Fand threatened to cut out her tongue
OL,8,Fif she went to the police. She was a
OL,9,Fslave in her own home, until rescue
OL,10,Ffinally came.
OL,12,FModern slavery is the darkest
OL,13,Funderbelly of our societies, now
OL,14,Ffinding an all too easy home online
OL,15,Fand well as in the real world, with
OL,16,Fchildren sold for sexual exploitation.
OL,17,FMy great colleagues Emma Murphy, Peter
OL,18,FSmith and Lucy Watson have all
OL,19,Freported on it too.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/15
